		<div class="trow_ ">
			<h2 class="trow_ cnt-center txt-blue tt_uc_ weight_600 fs-36_ mt-14_ mb-14_">Compliance Reward Participating Retail Pharmacy Terms & Conditions</h2>
		</div>

		<div class="bus-assoc-agrmnts">


            <p>The below terms and conditions are applicable to all prescriptions and commercially available products  participating in the Compliance Reward  program and its affiliates,   within  all  fifty  states,  the  District  of Columbia,  and applicable U.S. territories, including Puerto Rico, Guam, and the Virgin Islands. In accordance   with 42 C.F.R.   423.120(a)(8)(i),   Compliance Reward agrees  to  contract   with  any pharmacy  that is willing and able to accept and demonstrate  compliance  with the plans standard terms and conditions as described below and outlined in completeness  within the Pharmacy Participation  Agreement.</p>

            <div class="trow_ mb-14_">
                <p class="list-level1"><span class="list-number">1.</span>For Retail Pharmacy Services, Provider will discuss time to fill expectations with the Member when they present their prescription.</p>
                <p class="list-level1"><span class="list-number">2.</span>Participating Pharmacies must provide the same standard of service to Members that is provided to all other customers of the Participating Pharmacy.</p>
                <p class="list-level1"><span class="list-number">3.</span><strong>In the event the Participating Pharmacy participates in Medicaid, Medicare Part D or TRICARE contracts or any state or locality where copay assistance is prohibited,   Provider, and its Participating Pharmacies and their respective employed and/or contracted Pharmacists shall not use any component of  Compliance Reward Program to off-set  patients’ out of pocket prescription drug expenditures  and at all times must comply with all applicable Medicaid, Medicare Part D or TRICARE policies and procedures.</strong></p>
                <p class="list-level1"><span class="list-number">4.</span>Provider,  its Participating  Pharmacies  and their respective  employed and/or contracted  Pharmacists  shall fully adhere to all applicable state and federal laws, rules and regulations  including without limitation the Omnibus Budget Reconciliation  Act of 1990 regarding the professional  practice of pharmacy,  including, but not limited to, the review of patient profiles, evaluations  as to possible  drug interactions,  duplicate therapy,  and patient  counseling  on all new prescriptions  and on refill prescriptions  when warranted. A Pharmacist must be available and use best efforts to answer any   questions of the Member.</p>
                <p class="list-level1"><span class="list-number">5.</span>Provider and its Participating Pharmacies’ personnel will work with Compliance Reward in the enforcement   of Compliance Reward's preferred drug list, clinical programs, quality assurance, programs, and medication adherence programs.</p>
                <p class="list-level1"><span class="list-number">6.</span>Pharmacists and Pharmacy personnel must respond appropriately to all on-line messages provided as a part of the enrolled treatment process.   Messages may not be blocked by the Provider or its Participating Pharmacies.</p>
                <p class="list-level1"><span class="list-number">7.</span>Neither  Provider,  nor  any  Participating  Pharmacy  may  advertise  using  the  name of Compliance Reward unless written permission is obtained in advance and in writing from Compliance Reward, however Provider may announce or state in writing   the   are a Participating  Pharmacy that accepts Compliance Reward digital engagement program.</p>
                <p class="list-level1"><span class="list-number">8.</span>Provider and its Participating Pharmacies shall not provide pharmaceutical manufacturers or independent agency(s) working with manufacturers the name and address of any Compliance Reward Member or prescription information of a   Compliance Reward Member or prescriber under any circumstances.</p>
                <p class="list-level1"><span class="list-number">9.</span>Provider agrees  to comply  with  Compliance Reward 's  credentialing  process  which  in certain  regions  may include on-site inspections by Compliance Reward or Compliance Reward 's designee,  validation of historical pharmacy  purchasing and dispensing  records, minimal operating  time frame requirements,  review of ownership,  liability insurance and applicable pharmacy and pharmacist licensure status.</p>
                <p class="list-level1"><span class="list-number">10.</span>For physician who are dispensing providers, Participating Providers agree physician and for applicable dispensing provider’s provider organization agree to remain  in good  standing  as a network  participant  in Compliance Reward 's medical provider network for applicable provider/physician services only.</p>
            </div>
			
            <div class="trow_ ">
				<h2 class="trow_ cnt-center txt-blue tt_uc_ weight_600 fs-36_ mt-14_ mb-14_">RETAIL PHARMACY PROVIDER AGREEMENT</h2>
			</div>
			
			<div class="trow_ mb-14_">
				<p class="left-indent-4p">This Retail Pharmacy Provider Agreement (this "Agreement"), dated as of <span class="field-placeholder" style="width: 120px;">{{date('m/d', strtotime($practice->businessAgreement->rp_accepted_terms_dt))}}, {{date('Y', strtotime($practice->businessAgreement->rp_accepted_terms_dt))}}</span> (the "Effective Date"), is between Compliance Reward, LP ("Company"), located at 3201 Fannin Lane Southlake, TX 76092 and<span class="field-placeholder" style="width: 120px;">{{$practice->businessAgreement->rp_accepted_terms_user}}</span>("Provider"), <span class="field-placeholder" style="width: 120px;">{{$practice->practice_name}}</span>, located at <span class="field-placeholder" style="width: 120px;">{{$practice->practice_address}}</span>. Company and Provider are sometimes individually referred to as "Party" and collectively referred to as the "Parties."</p>
				<p class="left-indent-4p"><strong>WHEREAS,</strong> Company and Provider desire to contract such that Provider and Participating Pharmacies may engage designated Compliance Reward network(s) and provide Compliance Services to Members. This Agreement may be modified from time to time in the form of a written instrument signed by both Parties (an "Amendment"). The terms of any Amendment executed during this Agreement will be subject to the terms of this Agreement unless otherwise stipulated in the Amendment.</p>
				
				<div class="trow_ mb-14_">
					<p class="list-level1"><span class="list-number">1.</span> <strong>Scope of Activities.</strong> The Parties will undertake the following activities. Compliance Services to supply Provider and Participating Pharmacies with Digital Payment Card generation and administration, Member activity monitoring and facilitation, “Chat” capabilities for Members, Provider and Prescriber and access to Compliance Reward web-portal. Provider to compensate Compliance Reward according to <strong>Pricing and Payment Schedule attached hereto</strong>. The Parties acknowledge that their respective obligations to undertake these activities serve as good and valuable consideration for this Agreement.</p>
					<p class="list-level1"><span class="list-number">2. DEFINITIONS</span> <br> <span style="border-bottom: 1px solid black">“Account Provisioning Fee” “APF”</span> means fee related to the creation, individual compliance tracking and statistics for each product or service enrolled into the Compliance Service. The provisioned account allows instantaneous visibility, creation of algorithms to support a fully automated microtransaction tracking and compliance reporting to HCP’s, Participating Provider, and Member using the Compliance Services.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">"Affiliated Entity" means an entity that, during the applicable time, (a) shares at least one principal or owner or member  or pharmacist  in charge with Provider  or a Participating  Pharmacy;  or (b) owns,  in whole or in part, Provider or a Participating Pharmacy; or (c) is owned, in whole or in part, by Provider or a Participating  Pharmacy;  or  (d)  shares  the  same  NCPDP  or NPI  or  state  license  as Provider  or a Participating  Pharmacy;  or (e) is owned, in whole or in part, by the spouse, former spouse, parent, child, son-in-law,  daughter-in-law,  grandparent  or grandchild  of at least one principal  or owner or member of Provider or a Participating Pharmacy. This definition includes current Affiliated Entities and an entity that becomes an Affiliated Entity after the execution of this Agreement.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">“Applicable Prescription” means a filled or refilled prescription that a Provider Pharmacy elects to provide a Statement Credit awarded to Members who enroll and participate in the Compliance Services</p>
					<p class="list-level1">“Assistance Authorized”- means the total Patient Out of Pocket requested  by Participating Provider for those enrolled into the Compliance Reward program which are transferred to the Patient’s DPC.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">Balance Transfer – means Assistance Authorized submitted within the Web Portal by Participating Pharmacy for an Applicable Prescription into the Compliance Reward program which are applied to the Member’s DPC.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">“Base Engagement Fee”-means the fee paid by Participating Pharmacy to Compliance Reward per prescription filled or refilled utilizing the Compliance Reward program infrastructure for basic Compliance Services <strong>without</strong> accessing a Statement Credit.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">"Compliance Services" means digital compliance reminders and member education which enhances patient participation and ongoing compliance to their treatments regardless if the Member is eligible to receive Promotional Statement Credits.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">“Days’ Supply”- means the Participating Pharmacy stated number of days that an enrolled prescription should last Member if that prescription is taken as per instructions provided by prescribing physician.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">"Digital Payment Card”, “DPC” means the Compliance Reward Digital Payment Card included with the mobile application that identifies an individual as a Member provided by Compliance Reward. The DPC is used account for reward points accumulated by Member activities for digital education and compliance enhancing services provided for by Program Sponsor(s).</p>
					<p class="list-level1">“DPC Transaction Fee” means amount of fees paid by Participating Pharmacy for each prescription filled utilizing a DPC Authorized Assistance transaction.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">"Effective Date" means the date upon which the parties will begin performance under this Agreement as set forth on the signature page to this Agreement.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">“Health Care Provider” “HCP”,  means a Doctor of medicine or osteopathy, podiatrist, dentist, chiropractor, clinical psychologist, optometrist, nurse practitioner, physician assistant,  nurse mid-wife, or a clinical social worker who is authorized to practice by the State and performing with the scope of their practice as defined by State law.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">"Member" means an eligible individual that has been chosen by Participating Pharmacy to receive Compliance Services. Members with prescriptions that employ a Commercial Insurance Carrier or Self Pay  may enroll Applicable Prescription(s)and receive  an Statement Credit of up to $250 per Applicable Prescription to be used towards Members purchase of item(s) at the Participating Pharmacy such as their prescription or other qualifying purchase from a participating Compliance Reward pharmacy in good standing. Prescription(s) also may be enrolled WITHOUT Statement Credit at the expense of the participating pharmacy to receive Compliance Services. All purchased items such as prescriptions- enrolled to receive Statement Credit must not be designated Medicaid, Medicare or other forms of public insurance such as TRICARE <strong>or any state or locality</strong> which expressly prohibit any form of copayment or financial obligation assistance.  In addition, “Member"  may  include  eligible  individuals  for which  Compliance Reward provides digital education and compliance enhancing services on   behalf  of  affiliates,   employers, insurance  carriers, health  care services plans, third party administrators, self-administered or self-insured programs  providing  health  care  benefits, insurers, pharmacy  benefit  management  companies,  and other health related entities and/or other payors.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">"Network" means the network(s) of health care professionals and/or health care providers designated as participating providers and contracted with Compliance Reward for the provision of Compliance Services to Members.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">"Participating Pharmacy" means a Pharmacy owned, operated by, and/or under contract with Provider which provides Pharmacy Services. The term "Participating Pharmacy” includes Provider if Provider provides  Pharmacy Services.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">"Participating Pharmacy Service Standards” means those  performance   standards   set  out  and identified in Exhibit A, Participating Pharmacy Service Standards,  of this Agreement.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">“Patient Out of Pocket”- means the sum amount of fees, copays and coinsurance that a Participating Pharmacy is to collect from Member for prescription drug services for a prescription as communicated to Participating Pharmacy by Third Party Payer.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">“Payment Assistance Statement Credits”- means the amount of monies used to reduce Members out of pocket expenditure for purchase of drug treatments as communicated by Participating Provider in Compliance Reward software application under the field labeled “Assistance Authorized”.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">"Pharmacist" means  an individual  who is required  to be licensed  to practice  pharmacy  in the state and/or states where such individual is located and/or where Pharmacy Services are rendered and who is employed by or under contract with Provider and/or Participating Pharmacy.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">"Pharmacy" means a pharmacy licensed to do business in the state and/or states where it is located and where Pharmacy Services are rendered.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">"Pharmacy Reimbursement" means the amounts to be paid to Provider for the provision of 3rd party payors.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">"Pharmacy Services" includes  Retail  Pharmacy  Services meaning  those prescription  drugs and allied services and/or supplies  normally  provided  by Participating  Pharmacies  to the general  public  in the ordinary course of pharmacy business  to Members  at retail Pharmacies,  and Members not residing in long term care and/or assisted living facilities.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">“Pricing and Payment Schedule” includes Compliance Reward Fee schedule, start and end date for compliance Reward services.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">“Profit Share” See, “Rx Profitability” for details.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">“Program Sponsor” means any entity providing resources and support for the project, Compliance Services program.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">“Provider” means a wholly owned and operated Pharmaceutical Entity and its Participating Pharmacies and their respective employed and/or contracted Pharmacists including all ancillary staff members and technicians.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">“Quantity”- means the metric quantity of unit(s) in a prescription dispensed to Member by Participating Pharmacy.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">“Rx Ingredient Cost”-means the amount of monies paid by Participating Provider for a given prescription drug, pharmaceutical or applicable product less any additional discounts, credits, or rebates pursuant to Participating Provider’s terms with drug wholesaler or distributor or pharmaceutical manufacturer.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">“Rx Profitability”-means the estimated amount of profitability the Participating Pharmacy receives on an Applicable Prescription that is submitted to Compliance Reward for an enrolled Member. “Rx Profitability” equals the <strong>sum</strong> of “Third Party Paid” <strong>plus</strong> “Patient Out of Pocket” <strong>minus</strong> the <strong>sum</strong> of “Assistance Authorized” plus “Rx Ingredient Cost”.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">“Self-Pay” means someone who chooses to pay for their treatment directly rather than using private health insurance.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">“Statement Credit”- means funds provided by Program Sponsor per Applicable Prescription which are credited to Member’s DPC as communicated through the Compliance Reward application and is established by Participating Provider in Compliance Reward software application under the field labeled “Assistance Authorized”.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">“Third Party Paid”- means the total amount of reimbursement (for professional service fees plus prescription or OTC product costs) the Participating Pharmacy will receive from a third-party payer pursuant to Participating Pharmacy /Third Party payer contract terms</p>
					<p class="list-level1">"User(s)" is a person who has registered or is registered by the Access Administrator to use Compliance Reward's pharmacy provider Web Portal.</p>
					<p class="list-level1">"Web Portal" is a secured Compliance Reward website, accessed by Provider and their Participating Pharmacies through the internet, used for the intended purpose of accessing Member eligibility and enrolling applicable products.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="trow_ mb-14_">
					<p class="list-level1"><span class="list-number">3.PROVIDER SERVICES AND RESPONSIBILITIES.</span><br>Provider hereby agrees and represents, for itself and Participating Pharmacies, as follows:</p>
					<p class="list-level1"><strong>Prescription Drug Compliance Services</strong>.   Provider shall exercise sound judgement to determine which item(s) to enroll directly or cause to be enrolled by Participating Pharmacies to receive Compliance Services in connection to the medication or other product /service available by participating Compliance Reward Pharmacies. Prescriptions without payment system statement credits-which are intended to improve compliance and patient connectivity with their HCP or Pharmacy may be enrolled at the Participating Pharmacy performing    Pharmacy Services at the Member's request  in accordance with this Agreement and the applicable Plan(s) through online communication  by Compliance Reward.  Such Plans may be revised from time to time by Compliance Reward, at its discretion.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">a. Services</span>Provider   shall  provide,  or  arrange   for  the  provision   through   Participating   Pharmacies, Pharmacy  Services  to Members  in accordance  with the terms and conditions  of this Agreement  and in the  same  manner   as  such  Pharmacy   Services   are  provided   in  the   ordinary   course   of  business.  Upon Member presentation or database confirmation of a valid Compliance Reward Digital Payment  Card by a Member,  Provider  shall perform  and/or shall  require   Participating   Pharmacies   to  perform   the  following:   i)   when   operating   in  an  online environment, verify and qualify source of any insurance coverage(s); ii) Enroll the patient/member with the corresponding Compliance Reward offering based on their eligibility for one of the participating compliance  programs according  to the Member's Plan; iii) collect  from  the  Member of the Participating  Pharmacy's remaining out of pocket obligation. Compliance Reward will make available to its Participating Pharmacy (from within the Pharmacy Administrator Web Portal)evidence acceptable to Commercial Payors of any transactions supporting Copayment collections and expect Providers to develop, implement and maintain acceptable procedures necessary for the proper administration of this Agreement at its own expense accreditation and Licensure.   Provider  hereby  represents  that  each  Participating  Pharmacy,  and  their respective  employed  and/or contracted  Pharmacists,  have,  and shall maintain  in good  standing  for the term of this Agreement,  all federal,  state,  and local licenses,  accreditation  and certifications  as required by law.   Evidence of maintaining such licenses and certifications shall be submitted to Compliance Reward upon written request.</p>
					<p style="margin-bottom:36px;"></p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">b. Terms of Payment</span> Compliance Reward will submit an invoice to Provider for fees and charges associated with the Provider’s applicable <strong>Pricing and Payment Schedule</strong> attached and the applicable compensable events. Invoicing and payments are governed by the credit decision issued to Provider by Compliance Reward. Payments for invoices will be overdue if unpaid after the due date listed on the invoice. Overdue invoices will accrue interest at the statutory interest rates then in effect. Payments are subject to any and all applicable taxes and shall be paid in accordance with the payment method selected. All payments will be made in U.S. Dollars. Failure to provide an invoice will not relieve Provider of any liability or obligation hereunder.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">c. Compliance With Law</span> Provider shall comply and require Participating  Pharmacies  and all Pharmacists employed  by  or  under  contract  with  Provider  and/or  Participating   Pharmacies  to  comply,  with  all federal, state, and local statutes, ordinances, orders, rules  and regulations, and Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services (“CMS”) guidance  that are applicable to the provision of Pharmacy Services under terms and conditions of this Agreement.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">d. Authority to Bind Participating Pharmacies</span>Provider   hereby   represents   and   warrants   that the Participating   Pharmacies   will participate in designated Network(s) and comply with the terms and conditions of this Agreement.  Provider  is entering  into this Agreement  on behalf of itself and Participating Pharmacies and represents that it has been  authorized  and  shall  continue  to possess  the  authority  to bind  said  Participating  Pharmacies, individually and as part of or under contract with Provider, to all terms and conditions contained in this Agreement.   Provider shall provide at least thirty (30) calendar days’ prior written notice to Compliance Reward of any change in the location, significant change in the operating hours, closing or change in ownership of any Participating Pharmacy.    Notwithstanding anything  to the contrary  in this Agreement, if the relocation, change  in operating  hours, closing  or change in ownership  of any Participating  Pharmacy  significantly  affects  the availability  of Pharmacy Services  to Members  or individuals covered  under  this Agreement, Compliance Reward,  at its discretion, may terminate this Agreement upon fourte	en (14) calendar days' prior written notice to Provider. Additionally , Compliance Reward at its discretion,  may enroll affected Members (affected by the location, significant change in the operating hours, closing or change in ownership  of any  Participating  Pharmacy affecting availability of Pharmacy Services) with another Compliance Reward Provider or participating pharmacy.  In the event of a change in ownership of Participating   Pharmacies, the new owner  must  execute  a  new  Pharmacy  Provider  Agreement  with  Compliance Reward. Participating Pharmacies will only be added upon prior approval by Compliance Reward and such approval shall be dependent upon Compliance Reward's review of credentialing requirements.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">e. Sole Responsibilities</span> Provider shall be solely responsible for all advice provided to and Pharmacy Services  performed   for  Members  by  Provider  and/or  Participating   Pharmacies   and  their  respective employed  and/or contracted Pharmacists. <strong>Neither Compliance Reward, the Website, the Application, nor the Services should be used for or be considered medical advice for any member medical problem or condition.</strong></p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">f. Participant Identification</span> The Compliance Reward mobile application and Digital Payment Card are used and serve to identify the Member.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">g. Pharmacy Service Standards.</span>Provider, Participating  Pharmacies, and their respective  employed  and/or contracted   Pharmacists   shall  adhere  to  the  Participating   Pharmacy   Service   Standards   set  out  and identified   in  Exhibit  A, <i>Participating  Pharmacy  Service Standards</i>,  which  is attached  hereto  and incorporated into this Agreement by reference.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">h.	Compliance Reward Policies and Procedures.</span>   Provider, Participating  Pharmacies, and their respective  employed and/or   contracted   Pharmacists   shall   abide   by   all   compliance   program   requirements   and   any administrative  policies and procedures  established and revised by Compliance Reward from time to time, including quality  assurance,  quality  improvement, utilization  review,   and fiscal policies and procedures.  Provider shall be notified of any revisions to the compliance program and the policies and procedures which impact Provider’s and/or  Participating  Pharmacies'  responsibilities and/or obligations under the Agreement and they shall become binding fourteen (14) calendar days.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">i.	No Solicitation.</span>Provider, Participating Pharmacy, and their Pharmacists and personnel shall not solicit any Member to transfer any Covered   Service, unless Provider or  Participating  Pharmacy  receives Compliance Reward's permission  to perform  such solicitation.   This Section shall not apply if the Member initiates contact with Provider or Participating Pharmacy or the transfer is due to the addition of a new Participating Pharmacy or a closing of a Participating   Pharmacy  currently  providing   the  Service.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">j.	Compliance Reward Pharmacy Solutions Pharmacy Manual.</span> Provider shall comply with all requirements outlined in the Compliance Reward Pharmacy Manual.  This Agreement shall control in the event of a conflict between the Agreement and the Compliance Reward Pharmacy Solutions Pharmacy Manual.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">k. Security Breach.</span> Provider, Participating Pharmacy, and their Pharmacists shall provide alerts as to any potential security breach.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="trow_ mb-14_">
					<p class="list-level1"><span class="list-number">4</span> <strong>COMPLIANCE REWARD RESPONSIBILITIES. </strong></p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">a. Member Identification.</span>Compliance Reward, as  applicable,  shall  furnish  to  Members access to the Compliance Reward mobile application which serves as the only valid Identification Card with the name or names of the person(s) entitled to benefits imprinted, encoded, or referred to thereon.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">b. Compliance with Law.</span> Compliance Reward shall comply with all applicable federal and state laws and regulations, as well as CMS or TRICARE guidance to whether Compliance Reward may be offered for the digital engagement platform without any out of pocket assistance.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">c. Verification of Eligibility.</span>Compliance Reward requires our Participating Pharmacies to attest and verify eligibility of Members’ prescription(s) or services to receive out of pocket assistance. <strong>It is the sole responsibility of the Participating Pharmacies to refrain from offering any financial assistance to current Medicaid, Medicare Part D and TRICARE insurance carriers or in any state or locality where copay assistance is prohibited to the extent possible, will verify a Member's eligibility to receive Compliance Services.</strong></p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">d.	Marketing.</span>    Provider grants to Company a non-exclusive, non-transferable, royalty-free license to use Provider's trade names, trademarks, logos and service marks (collectively Marks) in connection with the performance of this Agreement. Company shall not use any of Provider 's Marks for any purpose without first obtaining the prior written advance consent of Provider. Company will not alter or permit alteration of, or remove or modify or permit removal or modification of, any of Provider 's, or other identifying marks placed by Provider or its agents on the products or associated documentation or literature, without Provider 's prior written approval. Except as specifically provided in this Agreement, nothing in this Agreement shall confer upon Company any right, title or interest in any of the Marks. or the registration thereof or attempt to register any trademarks, marks or trade names that are in any way confusingly similar to Provider ‘s Marks.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">e. </span>Company acknowledges that its utilization of Provider 's Marks will not create in it, nor will it represent it has, any right, title or interest in or to Provider s Marks other than the express and limited right to use Provider 's Marks on Company’s Website granted under this Agreement.</p>

				</div>
				<div class="trow_ mb-14_">
					<p class="list-level1"><span class="list-number">5</span> <strong>REIMBURSEMENT, MAINTENANCE, INSPECTION AND AUDIT</strong></p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">a.	Electronic Enrollment Submission.</span> Provider, Participating Pharmacies, and their respective employed and/or contracted Pharmacists shall utilize, at their expense, the online, electronic enrollment submission program of eligible product(s) or service(s) enrolled into the Compliance Reward platform. The purchase, cost, maintenance and usage  of electronic  transmission  line(s) and  interface equipment   is the responsibility   of Provider.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">b.	Timing of Payment.</span>   Compliance Reward,  or its designee,  agrees to convey Payment System Credits to Members’ DPC when authorized by Participating Pharmacy in the form of Payment Assistance Statement Credits  for Applicable Prescriptions,   and  for other Compliance Services rendered to  Participating Pharmacy  in accordance with Fees described  on Pricing and Payment Schedule.   Payment by Participating Pharmacy to Compliance Reward of these fees and Payment System Credits must be received by Compliance Reward in a timely fashion, but in no case may payment exceed more than fourteen (14) calendar days after invoice date.   Invoices will be developed and transmitted electronically to the Participating Pharmacies. In the event Participating Pharmacy is two (2) Business Days in arrears on payment of undisputed invoices under this Agreement, Compliance Reward has the right to discontinue providing Services for Members of the delinquent Covered Plan unless and until the undisputed amounts due and owing for such Covered Plan have been paid. If Participating Pharmacy is: (a) untimely in paying undisputed invoices three (3) times in any twelve month period, or (b) is delinquent by more than 4 (four) days in the payment of an undisputed invoice, Compliance Reward  has the right to deem such untimely payments a material breach of this agreement.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">c.Member Hold Harmless Clause.</span>  Provider hereby agrees and shall require Participating Pharmacies and their respective employed and/or contracted Pharmacists to agree that sponsorship for Compliance Services may be oversubscribed and no-longer available to the eligible member. In no event, insolvency or breach of this Agreement, shall Provider or Participating Pharmacies or their respective employed and/or contracted Pharmacists bill, charge, collect a deposit from, seek retroactive compensation, remuneration or reimbursement from, or have any recourse against a Member   or  persons  other  than  Compliance Reward  acting  on  their  behalf  for  Compliance Services  provided   by Provider  which  are  the  legal  obligation  of Compliance Reward.    This provision shall not prohibit collection of Out of Pocket obligations and charges for Compliance Services in accordance with the terms of this Agreement.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">d.	Maintenance and Retention of Records.</span>  Provider  agrees and shall require Participating  Pharmacies  to agree to maintain pharmacy  records  or data with respect to Members receiving  Compliance Services and Pharmacy Services, in a manner consistent with industry norms, prudent record keeping procedures, the requirements  of applicable  federal  and  state  laws,  rules  and regulations.  Compliance Reward,  or a third  party designated by Compliance Reward, or any government agency allowed by law, shall be entitled to conduct audits of any and all records  and prescription  files related  to and supporting  Compliance Services  and Pharmacy Services rendered to Members.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">e.	Review and Audit of Pharmacy Records.</span>  Compliance Reward and/or its duly authorized agents shall have the right to examine Provider's and/or Participating Pharmacies' records, prescription files and signature logs, for the purpose of verifying eligibility of Member information through an audit.  Verification in this context shall be limited to records pertaining to Compliance Services rendered to Members only and may be made at any time during the term of this Agreement,</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">f.	Claim Accuracy.</span> Provider agrees that Provider and Participating Pharmacies are responsible for accurate submission of all prescription Rx Ingredient Cost and claim information via appropriate claim transaction.    Such claims are subject to review pursuant <strong>Review and Audit of Pharmacy Records.</strong> Claims found to have inaccurate prescription or claim information submitted by Provider or Participating Pharmacies are subject to correction and/or recovery according   to Compliance Reward’s audit guidelines   and applicable   federal, state, or local  laws  or regulations  or CMS guidance.  When Provider and/or Participating  Pharmacies  cooperate with Compliance Reward's audit process and supply requested corrected claim information, Compliance Reward may, at its discretion and according to federal, state, or local laws or regulations or CMS guidance, elect to correct   such  inaccurate   Rx Enrollment  information   within   Compliance Reward's   systems.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">g.	Confidentiality   of Records.</span>    The  parties  hereto  agree  that  all  records  maintained  with  respect  to Pharmacy   Services   rendered   to  Members   and  personally   identifiable   information   shall  remain confidential, and shall not be released  absent proper execution  of all necessary  consent  forms, unless otherwise specifically provided herein to the contrary.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">h.	Personally, Identifiable Information.</span>   Provider agrees and shall require Participating Pharmacies and their respective   employed   and/or   contracted   Pharmacists   to  agree  that  medical   and  personally identifiable patient-specific  information  obtained in the course of dispensing medication to Members is confidential  medical  information.  Provider  further agrees  and shall require  Participating  Pharmacies  to agree that such information  may not be shared, distributed, marketed, transferred  or sold to any entity,  including  without  limitation  any "switching company", other than Provider or Compliance Reward, or its Claims Processor without the prior written consent of Compliance Reward, and where applicable execution of all necessary consent forms.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">i.</span>Provider and Participating Pharmacy shall alert Compliance Reward  within 5 business days of the discovery of a security breach including (i) any act or omission that materially compromises either the security, confidentiality or integrity of Member Information or the physical, technical, administrative or organizational safeguards put in place by the Provider or participating Pharmacy that relate to the protection of the security, confidentiality or integrity of Member Information, or (ii) receipt of a complaint in relation to the privacy practices of by the Provider or participating Pharmacy or a breach or alleged breach of this Agreement relating to such privacy practices.</p>
				</div>
