					<p class="list-level1"><span class="list-number">10. </span> <strong>TERM AND TERMINATION.</strong></p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">a. </span>The initial term of this Agreement shall be for  a period  of one  (1)  year commencing  on the Effective  Date, as defined on the signature page. Thereafter, this Agreement will automatically  renew for subsequent  one (1) year terms,  unless either party provides  written notice of non-renewal or termination to the other party at least fourteen (14) calendar days prior to end of the initial term noted in this Section or any subsequent renewal terms thereafter.   In addition, this Agreement may be terminated by the mutual written consent of both parties at any time.  Any notice of termination specified in this Agreement shall be delivered in accordance with Section on, Notices.  This Agreement supersedes any agreement currently in place between Provider and Compliance Reward or any of its affiliates for Pharmacy Services rendered by Participating Pharmacies to Members covered under this Agreement.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">b.	Termination upon Insolvency.</span>  Either party may terminate this Agreement immediately upon the filing by or against the other party of any action under the Federal Bankruptcy  Act, or any other law or act regarding  insolvency, reorganization, arrangement, or extension for the relief of debtors, including the assignment of assets for the benefit  of creditors, and the appointment  of receiver  or trustee  for transfer  or sale of a material portion of the other party's assets.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">c.	Compliance Reward Termination.</span>    Notwithstanding   anything  to  the  contrary  in this  Agreement,  Compliance Reward  may terminate this Agreement, in its entirety or, in its sole discretion, with respect to specific Participating Pharmacies,   immediately,   with  no  cure  period,   upon  written  notice,   stating  the  cause  for  such  event:   (i)   Compliance Reward   determines   that   the   continued   participation   of  Provider, Participating  Pharmacy,  or any Pharmacist under this Agreement may not be enrolling Eligible members, or  adversely affect the health,  safety or welfare  of any Member  or bring  Compliance Reward  or its health  care Networks  into  disrepute;  (ii) Compliance Reward determines  that Provider, Participating  Pharmacy,  or any Pharmacist  has made  a material misrepresentation   to  Compliance Reward  or  its  designee;  (iii)  Compliance Reward  determines  that  Provider,  Participating Pharmacy,  or  Pharmacist  has  violated  the  covenants  set  forth  in  <strong>Exhibit  A</strong>  <span style="font-style: italic">Participating  Pharmacy  Service  Standards;</span>  (iv)  Compliance Reward  loses  its authority  to do business  in total  or as to any limited  segment  of business, but then  only as to that segment;  (v) Provider,  Participating  Pharmacy,  or any Pharmacist  fails to comply with or provide requested documentation  to satisfy inspections and (vi) Compliance Reward's internal investigation  or audit reasonably  determined that Provider, Participating  Pharmacy, or Pharmacist  has violated applicable federal statutes or regulations, state statutes or regulations, or guidance from CMS or state boards  of pharmacy;  and (vii) Provider  is not compliant  with the Compliance Reward  Pharmacy  Manual, as amended from time to time.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">d.	Cure.</span>  In the event of a material breach of this Agreement by either party, the non-breaching party may terminate this Agreement upon at least fourteen (14) calendar days'  prior written notice to the breaching party, which notice shall specify in detail the nature of the alleged material breach; provided, however, that if the alleged material  breach  is susceptible  to cure, the breaching  party  shall have fourteen  (14) calendar days from the date of receipt of notice of termination to cure such breach, and if such breach is not cured to the non-breaching party's  satisfaction within the fourteen (14) calendar day period,  then the date of termination  shall be the date set forth in the notice of termination.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">e.	Without Cause Termination.</span>  Notwithstanding   anything  to  the  contrary  in  this  Agreement   and subsequent to the initial one (1) year term of the Agreement,  either party may terminate this Agreement at any time without  cause by giving the other party at least ninety (90) calendar  days'  prior written notice, which notice shall be in accordance with <span style="font-style:italic">Notices</span>.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">f.	Immediate Termination.</span>    If either  party  ceases  its operations,  or if a writ  of garnishment  or levy, attachment or execution relating to a debt of either party is served upon the other party and not removed within  ten  (l 0)  calendar  days  from  the  date  of such  service  this  Agreement  may  be  terminated immediately at the option of the other party, upon written notice as provided for in Notices. Upon receipt of such notice, both parties shall immediately  cease and terminate  operating under this Agreement, provided that payment shall be made to Provider for all claims mutually agreed upon to be paid  for  Compliance Services  rendered  hereunder  prior  to  termination.  This right shall be in addition to all other rights and remedies of the non-defaulting party as allowed by law or equity.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">g.	Contact with Members.</span>  In the event of the termination of this Agreement for any reason, Provider acknowledges and agrees that Compliance Reward may, in its discretion, contact impacted Members to inform them of Provider's or any participating Pharmacy’s termination.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">h.	Termination.</span> Providers and Participating Pharmacies are not eligible to contract with Compliance Reward for participation in any of its pharmacy networks for a minimum of one (1) year from the effective date of the termination.   If this Agreement   is terminated pursuant   to this Section.  Provider   agrees that Participating   Pharmacies   and Affiliated   Entities   are not eligible   to contract   with  Compliance Reward   for participation  in any of its pharmacy networks for a minimum of one (1) year from the effective date of the  termination.  Provider and Participating Pharmacies agree that this  provision  shall  apply  to  all Affiliated Entities, regardless of whether they are signatories to this Agreement.</p>
					<p class="list-level1"><span class="list-number">11. </span> <strong>DISPUTE RESOLUTION</strong></p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">a. </span>Internal   Dispute   Resolution.  Provider   acknowledges   and  agrees  and  shall  require   Participating Pharmacies  to acknowledge and agree that in the event it/he/she is unable to resolve directly disputes that may arise with Compliance Reward, Provider and/or Participating Pharmacies will exhaust all internal Compliance Reward administrative  appeal, grievance or other dispute resolution mechanisms prior to the submission of any unresolved disputes to binding arbitration in accordance with the provisions immediately below.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">b. </span>Agreement to Arbitrate. The parties agree that any dispute arising from or relating to this Agreement  or out of their business relationship  which cannot be settled by mutual agreement  shall be submitted to final  and binding  arbitration  under  the  Commercial  Arbitration  Rules  of the American  Arbitration Association   ("AAA"),   including  disputes  concerning  the  scope,  validity  or  applicability   of this Agreement to arbitrate ("Arbitration  Agreement").  The parties agree that this Arbitration Agreement is subject to, and shall be interpreted in accordance with, the Federal Arbitration Act, 9 U.S.C.  §§ 1-14. No claim or allegation shall be excepted from this Arbitration Agreement,  including an alleged breach of the Agreement, alleged violations of state or federal statutes or regulations, tort or other common law claims, and claims of any kind that a party to the Agreement has conspired or coordinated with, or aided and  abetted,  one  or  more  third  parties  in  violation  of law.  Without limiting the foregoing, this Arbitration Agreement requires arbitration of disputes involving antitrust, racketeering and similar claims. This Arbitration Agreement supersedes any prior arbitration agreement between the parties.  The parties agree to arbitrate disputes arising from the parties’ business relationship prior to the Effective</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">c. </span>Date of the Agreement under the terms of this arbitration provision and the parties also agree to arbitrate any disputes arising from or relating to the termination of this Agreement.  This Arbitration Agreement, however, does not revive any claims that were barred by the terms of prior contracts, by  applicable statutes of limitations  or otherwise.  The parties agree this Agreement is a transaction involving interstate commerce and therefore that the Federal Arbitration Act, 9 U.S.C.  §1 et seq. applies.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">d.	Arbitration Process.</span> The arbitration shall be conducted by one neutral arbitrator selected by the parties from a panel of arbitrators proposed by the AAA.   The arbitrator shall have prior professional, business or academic experience in healthcare, managed care or health insurance matters.   In the event of an arbitration   of antitrust   claims, the   arbitrator   shall have prior   professional, business, or academic experience in antitrust matters.    The arbitration shall be conducted in a location  selected  by  mutual agreement   or,  failing  agreement,  at  a  location  selected  by  the  AAA.    The cost of any arbitration proceeding(s) hereunder shall be borne equally by the parties.   Each party shall be responsible for its own attorneys' fees and such other costs and expenses incurred related to the proceedings, except to the extent the applicable substantive law specifically provides otherwise.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">e.	Joinder; Class Litigation.</span>  Any arbitration under this Arbitration Agreement shall be solely  between Compliance Reward and Provider,  shall not be joined  with another lawsuit, claim,  dispute or arbitration  commenced by any other person,  and may not be maintained  on behalf of any purported  class. Both parties waive the right to participate in any class action against the other, and the arbitrator has no authority to adjudicate any class claims or class arbitration.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">f.	Expense of Compelling Arbitration.</span>   If either party  commences  a judicial  proceeding  asserting  claims subject to this Arbitration  Agreement  or refuses to participate  in an arbitration  commenced  by the other party, and the other party  obtains  a judicial  order compelling  arbitration  of such claims, the party that commenced   the  judicial   proceeding   or  refused  to  participate   in  an  arbitration   in  violation   of this Arbitration   Agreement   shall  pay  the  other  party's  costs  incurred  in  obtaining  an  order  compelling arbitration, including the other party's reasonable  attorneys' fees.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">g.	Judgment on the Decision and Award.</span>   Judgment upon the decision and award rendered by an arbitrator under this Arbitration Agreement may be entered in any court having jurisdiction thereof.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">h. </span>Non-Signatory Affiliated Entities Bound to Arbitrate.  This section shall apply to any claims or disputes brought by non-signatory Affiliated Entities arising from or relating to any actions taken pursuant to this Agreement.</p>
