					<p class="list-level1"><span class="list-number"></span> <strong>Exhibit A, Participating Pharmacy Service Standards.</strong></p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">1.</span>The following General Participating Pharmacy Service Standards shall be met and maintained by Provider, each Participating Pharmacy, and their respective employed and/or contracted Pharmacists and personnel, as specified, providing all types of Pharmacy Services:</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">2.</span>Participating Pharmacy shall designate a point of contact under their employ, to serve as a liaison to support day to day interactions with Compliance Reward and Participating Pharmacy staff in support of developing specific P&Ps and accountabilities to ensure optimal use of the Compliance Reward offering</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">3.</span>Participating Pharmacy shall prepare and dispense prescription drugs and medications only upon receiving an order from a person licensed to prescribe prescription drugs; (ii) be duly licensed as a Pharmacy by the State Board of Pharmacy  in the state and/or states where such Participating  Pharmacy  is located and/or where services are rendered,  to the extent required by law;  and (iii) comply with all applicable  federal, state, and local laws, rules, and regulations, governing the practice of pharmacy.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">4.</span>Participating Pharmacy must provide the same standard of service to Members that Participating Pharmacy provides to all other customers of Participating Pharmacy.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">5.</span>Provider, Participating Pharmacy, and their respective employed and/or contracted Pharmacists shall fully comply with all applicable state and federal laws, rules and regulations  including without  limitation the Omnibus Budget Reconciliation  Act of 1990  regarding the professional  practice of pharmacy,  including, but not limited to,  the review of patient profiles,  evaluations  as to possible  drug interactions,  duplicate therapy, and patient  counseling  on all new prescriptions  and on refill prescriptions  when warranted. A Pharmacist must be available and use best efforts to answer any questions of the Member.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">6.</span>Participating Pharmacy shall ensure that Members are serviced in a friendly, professional manner and that they receive their medication without unnecessary delays.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">7.</span>Pharmacists and Participating Pharmacy personnel shall respond appropriately to all electronic messages provided as a part of the claim’s registration process. Messages may not be blocked by Provider or Participating Pharmacy.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">8.</span>Neither Provider nor Participating Pharmacy may advertise using the name of Compliance Reward unless advance written permission is obtained from Compliance Reward; however, Provider and Participating Pharmacy may announce or state in writing they participate in the Network.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">9.</span>Provider and Participating Pharmacy shall not provide to pharmaceutical manufacturers or independent agencies working with pharmaceutical manufacturers  the name and address of any Member or prescription information of any Member or prescriber under any circumstances.</p>
					<p class="list-level2"><span class="list-number">10.</span>Participating Pharmacy shall provide Members access to an on-call Pharmacist for questions related to drug therapy.</p>
